The Kano State Government, on Tuesday, launched a comprehensive rural electrification scheme, targeted at over 100 rural communities across the state. The scheme, established by Shenzhen Lemi Technology Development and Lemi Renewable Electricity Limited, seeks to provide solar home systems to small rural communities. On completion, the scheme is expected to provide an individual, with solar power to be paid on installment. While launching the scheme in Kano, the Commissioner for Rural and Community Development, Musa Iliyasu Kwankwaso, said the project would also provide job opportunities for the teeming youths across the state and boost the socio-economic status of rural dwellers. He said to achieve the set objectives, the Kano State government signed an agreement with the company to provide solar facilities. He expressed the state governmentâ€™s preparedness to provide all the necessary social amenities across the 44 local government areas. In his remarks, the state Commissioner for Local Government and Chieftaincy Affairs, Alhaji Murtala Garo, represented by the Special Adviser on Local Governments, Alhaji Laminu Sani, commended the state government for the good gesture to the people. The Country Manager of Shenzhen Lemi Technology Limited, Monica Liang, who signed the Memorandum of Understanding, said the company would provide durable and quality equipment for the project. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com